  "local_port": 46714,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I uninstall Modified apk by Lucky Patcher (I can only deactivate it)?",
  "response": "Uninstalling a modified APK created by Lucky Patcher can sometimes be tricky since these modifications can alter the original application's behavior and even its uninstall procedure. Here are some methods you can try to fully uninstall the modified APK:\n\n### Method 1: Using Android Settings\n1. **Open Settings**: Go to your device's settings.\n2. **Apps or Application Manager**: Navigate to 'Apps' or 'Application Manager' depending on your device.\n3. **Find the App**: Scroll down and find the app you want to uninstall.\n4. **Uninstall**: Tap on the app and select 'Uninstall'. If you can only deactivate it, proceed to the following methods.\n\n### Method 2: Using Lucky Patcher\n1. **Open Lucky Patcher**: Launch the Lucky Patcher app.\n2. **Find the App**: Scroll through the list of apps and find the modified APK.\n3. **Uninstall**: Tap on the app and choose 'Uninstall App'. Lucky Patcher may be able to remove it completely.\n\n### Method 3: Using a Third-Party Uninstaller\n1. **Install a Third-Party App**: Download a third-party app uninstaller from the Google Play Store, such as 'App Manager', 'Easy Uninstaller', or 'Uninstall Master'.\n2. **Open the Uninstaller**: Launch the app and let it load all the installed applications.\n3. **Find the App**: Locate the app you want to uninstall.\n4. **Uninstall**: Select the app and follow the prompts to uninstall it.\n\n### Method 4: Using ADB (Android Debug Bridge)\n1. **Enable Developer Options**: Go to 'Settings' > 'About Phone' and tap 'Build Number' seven times to enable Developer Options.\n2. **Enable USB Debugging**: In 'Settings' > 'Developer Options', enable 'USB Debugging'.\n3. **Install ADB**: Download and install ADB on your computer.\n4. **Connect Device**: Connect your Android device to the computer via USB.\n5. **Open Command Prompt/Terminal**: Open Command Prompt (Windows) or Terminal (macOS/Linux).\n6. **Enter ADB Commands**: Type the following commands:\n    ```\n    adb devices\n    adb shell pm list packages\n    adb shell pm uninstall -k --user 0 <package_name>\n    ```\n   Replace `<package_name>` with the actual package name of the app you want to uninstall.\n\n### Method 5: Factory Reset (last resort)\n1. **Backup Data**: Ensure all your important data is backed up.\n2. **Open Settings**: Go to 'Settings'.\n3. **System**: Navigate to 'System'.\n4. **Reset Options**: Tap on 'Reset options'.\n5. **Factory Reset**: Choose 'Erase all data (factory reset)' and confirm.\n\n### Notes:\n- **Root Access**: If your device is rooted, you may have more control over app removal using root file managers like \"Root Explorer\".\n- **Data Loss**: Uninstalling apps may result in data loss associated with the app. Ensure you have backups if needed.\n\nIf none of these methods work, you might need to seek assistance from forums or communities like XDA Developers, where advanced troubleshooting related to modified APKs and device-specific issues are discussed.",
